getSimilarityMaxIC

public OwlSim.ScoreAttributeSetPair getSimilarityMaxIC(org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLNamedIndividual i,
                                                       org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLNamedIndividual j)
Description copied from interface: OwlSim
Find the inferred attribute shared by both i and j that has highest IC. If there is a tie then the resulting structure will have multiple classes. 
 MaxIC(i,j) = max { IC(c) : c ∈ LCS(i,j) }
 CMaxIC(i,j) =  { c : c ∈ LCS(i,j), IC(c) = MaxIC(i,j) }
As a convenience, this method also returns the LCS class as well as the IC This is the same metric used by Lord et al in Investigating semantic similarity measures across the Gene Ontology: the relationship between sequence and annotation.

Specified by:
getSimilarityMaxIC in interface OwlSim
Returns:
MaxIC(i,j)

createElementAttributeMapFromOntology

public void createElementAttributeMapFromOntology()
Description copied from interface: OwlSim
This must be called prior to calculation of any similarity metrics. It creates a set of attribute classes (the subset of classes that have inferred or direct individuals) and the set of elements (individuals), together with any internal indexing assumes that the ontology contains both attributes (TBox) and elements + associations (ABox)
